  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Uncertainty quantification has been performed across material property and geometric tolerances using Monte Carlo sampling (n=2000 draws). A plan to extend the current UQ framework with a formal sensitivity analysis — ranking the relative contributions of titanium alloy elastic modulus, screw-rod interface friction coefficient, and vertebral body surrogate stiffness — is documented in the project workplan but has not yet been executed; dominant input drivers therefore remain uncharacterized at this submission date.",
