      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum linear-elastic Ti-6Al-4V with nonlinear contact at screw-rod interface; plasticity captured via bilinear isotropic hardening. Required gradation 3.",
      "rationale": "Model physics includes geometric nonlinearity (large-displacement formulation), bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V (E=114 GPa, sigma_y=880 MPa, Et=1.2 GPa), and augmented Lagrange contact at screw-rod and screw-vertebral body interfaces. Model form judged representative of dominant physical mechanisms. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certificate of conformance; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test articles. Required gradation 3. UQ performed via Monte Carlo sampling across input distributions; sensitivity analysis planned for future submission cycle.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy material properties (elastic modulus, yield strength, tangent modulus) assigned from lot-specific certificate of conformance values. Screw and rod geometry digitized via CMM to ±0.01 mm. Vertebral body surrogate (UHMWPE block) stiffness measured per test protocol. Monte Carlo UQ (n=2000) propagates uncertainty in material properties and geometric tolerances through all three QoIs; coefficient of variation on predicted stiffness 3.1%, yield force 4.8%, force at 40 mm 5.6%. We plan to extend with sensitivity analysis to rank dominant input drivers in a subsequent submission; this ranking is not available for the current package. Gradation 3 achieved on the basis of documented UQ coverage."
    },
    {
