      "rationale": "The three QoIs are the primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and directly relate to clinical performance: construct stiffness governs load sharing, yield force indicates onset of permanent deformation, and force at 40 mm represents post-yield load-bearing capacity relevant to implant fracture risk. Gradation 2 achieved."
